Former president Jacob Zuma faces a contempt of court order brought by the state capture inquiry. Editor's note: This Livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - The Constitutional Court is due to hear an urgent application for former president Jacob Zuma to be declared in contempt of court. The application stems from Zuma's failure to comply with the court's order that he must comply with summonses and directives issued by the state capture inquiry READ: Zuma hits out at Zondo's 'politics' Zuma is alleged to have willfully refused to appear before the commission, and file any affidavits, despite being requested to do so.